A very simple image slider jQuery plugin.

Usage:

1) In the document head, include CSS file:
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="kkslide/jquery.kkslide.css" />

2) Place the images in a <div> along with a <div> for the loading icon:
	<div class="mySliderName" style="height:270px;width:570px;">
		<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/jliba/4665625073/" title="145.365 - Happy Bokeh Thursday! | Flickr - Photo Sharing!" target="_blank"><img src="http://slidesjs.com/examples/standard/img/slide-1.jpg" width="570" height="270" alt="Slide 1" border="0"></a>
		<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/stephangeyer/3020487807/" title="Taxi | Flickr - Photo Sharing!" target="_blank"><img src="http://slidesjs.com/examples/standard/img/slide-2.jpg" width="570" height="270" alt="Slide 2" border="0"></a>
		<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/childofwar/2984345060/" title="Happy Bokeh raining Day | Flickr - Photo Sharing!" target="_blank"><img src="http://slidesjs.com/examples/standard/img/slide-3.jpg" width="570" height="270" alt="Slide 3" border="0"></a>
		<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/aftab/3152515428/" title="Save my love for loneliness | Flickr - Photo Sharing!" target="_blank"><img src="http://slidesjs.com/examples/standard/img/slide-7.jpg" width="570" height="270" alt="Slide 7" border="0"></a>
		<div id="loader" class="loader"></div>
	</div>
	
3) At the end of the document, before the closing <body> tag, include the JS file:
	<script type="text/javascript" src="kkslide/jquery.kkslide.js"></script>
	
4) Once the document has loaded, call the slider function and set the options:
	<script type="text/javascript">
		$(document).ready(function() {
			$('.mySliderName').kkSlide({
				hoverPause: true,
				speed: 3500,
				transition: 'slide'
			});
		});
	</script>

5) If jQuery-ui is enabled, you have additional easing options.  For more info, visit http://jqueryui.com/demos/effect/easing.html
